The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for solving problems on graphs. The main focus is on maximum matching width and its alternative definitions, which are related to graph decompositions and tree-like structures. The paper also presents a fast algorithm for Dominating Set based on maximum matching width, which is a classic problem in graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper involves some aspects of graph theory and combinatorics, which suggest cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as possible sub-categories.
